tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE experiments (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    experiment_name TEXT,
    start_date TIMESTAMP,
    end_date TIMESTAMP,
    num_layers INT,
    status TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE results (
    result_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    experiment_id INT REFERENCES experiments(id),
    result_data JSON,
    accuracy FLOAT,
    loss FLOAT,
    execution_time INT
);

CREATE TABLE experiments (
    experiment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    experiment_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    experiment_description TEXT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP,
    completed BOOLEAN
);

CREATE TABLE results (
    result_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    experiment_id INT REFERENCES experiments(experiment_id),
    result_value FLOAT,
    result_description TEXT,
    result_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE networks (
    network_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    network_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    network_type VARCHAR(50),
    layers INT,
    neurons_per_layer INT
);

CREATE TABLE results (
    result_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    experiment_id INT,
    result_value FLOAT,
    result_description TEXT,
    FOREIGN KEY (experiment_id) REFERENCES experiments(experiment_id)
);

CREATE TABLE layers (
    layer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id INT,
    layer_name VARCHAR(100),
    layer_type VARCHAR(50),
    FOREIGN KEY (model_id) REFERENCES models(model_id)
);

CREATE TABLE experiments (
    experiment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    experiment_name VARCHAR(255),
    experiment_description TEXT,
    start_date TIMESTAMP,
    end_date TIMESTAMP,
    dataset_used VARCHAR(100)
);

CREATE TABLE models (
    model_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    model_name VARCHAR(255),
    model_description TEXT,
    model_type VARCHAR(50),
    training_time INT
);

CREATE TABLE hyperparameters (
    hyperparameter_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    experiment_id INT,
    hyperparameter_name VARCHAR(100),
    hyperparameter_value FLOAT,
    FOREIGN KEY (experiment_id) REFERENCES experiments(experiment_id)
);

CREATE TABLE results (
    result_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    experiment_id INT,
    model_id INT,
    result_metrics JSONB,
    execution_time FLOAT,
    FOREIGN KEY (experiment_id) REFERENCES experiments(experiment_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (model_id) REFERENCES models(model_id)
);

CREATE TABLE execution_logs (
    log_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    experiment_id INT,
    log_timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    log_message TEXT,
    FOREIGN KEY (experiment_id) REFERENCES experiments(experiment_id)
);
